</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1596,1800]" pageId="3" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,463,1596,1621]" pageId="3" pageNumber="418">Record on halacarid mite:</emphasis>
Several specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Viets, 1938)" authorityName="Viets" authorityYear="1938" baseAuthorityName="Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[714,1181,1596,1621]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Copidognathus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricorneatus">
<emphasis box="[714,1029,1596,1621]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="418">Copidognathus tricorneatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1043,1173,1596,1621]" pageId="3" pageNumber="418" refId="ref11858" refString="Viets, K. (1938) Uber eine neue Art von Meresmilben, Copidognathus tricorneata Lohmann (Halacaridae, Acari). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 122, 127 - 132." type="journal article">Viets, 1938</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
collected from eastern Аustralia near Sydney between corals and sponges were infested with the suctorian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Claparede &amp; Lachmann" authorityYear="1859" box="[1157,1335,1631,1656]" class="Kinetofragminophora" family="Dendrosomididae" genus="Ophryodendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Suctorida" pageId="3" pageNumber="418" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1157,1335,1631,1656]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="418">Ophryodendron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. The suctorians were observed predominantly on legs but also on idiosoma of mites (
<bibRefCitation box="[1043,1170,1668,1693]" pageId="3" pageNumber="418" refId="ref11858" refString="Viets, K. (1938) Uber eine neue Art von Meresmilben, Copidognathus tricorneata Lohmann (Halacaridae, Acari). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 122, 127 - 132." type="journal article">Viets 1938</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="418" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1596,1800]" pageId="3" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1703,1728]" pageId="3" pageNumber="418">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[324,463,1703,1728]" pageId="3" pageNumber="418" refId="ref11858" refString="Viets, K. (1938) Uber eine neue Art von Meresmilben, Copidognathus tricorneata Lohmann (Halacaridae, Acari). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 122, 127 - 132." type="journal article">Viets (1938)</bibRefCitation>
did not include the description and figures from found suctorian specimens. Thus, it is impossible to determine what representative species of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stein" authorityYear="1867" box="[896,1092,1740,1765]" class="Phyllopharyngea" family="Ophryodendridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Exogenida" pageId="3" pageNumber="418" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="family">Ophryodendridae</taxonomicName>
was found. It is quite possible that the suctorian specimens represent the genus 
<emphasis box="[697,806,1775,1800]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="418">Corethria</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
